  "children": [],
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "1. Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Qualcomm Universal Peripheral (QUP) is a highly flexible and programmable module for supporting a wide range of serial interfaces (I2C, SPI, UART, and QSPI).",
        "There are five SAILSS_QUP serial engines (SEs) available in SAIL_I/Os (SAIL domain)",
        "Each QUP SE has up to seven lanes (I/O) numbered from 0 to 6"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20configure%20SAIL%20SPI/image-2024-10-28_13-7-41.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to configure SAIL SPI/image-2024-10-28_13-7-41.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "The supported assignments are listed in the table for each QUP",
        "Only one protocol can be selected in one QUP SE at a time. For example, simultaneous UART and I2C functionality are no longer supported"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20configure%20SAIL%20SPI/image-2024-10-28_12-46-16.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to configure SAIL SPI/image-2024-10-28_12-46-16.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20configure%20SAIL%20SPI/image-2024-10-23_17-15-49.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to configure SAIL SPI/image-2024-10-23_17-15-49.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "2. Limitations"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "SWS_Spi_00040:  SPI handler/driver handles only the Master mode. CDD for SPI slave driver will be planned."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "SWS_Spi_00050:  SPI handler/driver only supports full-duplex mode"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "SWS_Spi_00108:  Level 2 SPI handler/driver is specified for microcontrollers that must provide at least two SPI buses that use separated hardware units. Otherwise, this level of functionality does not make sense."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Only EB is supported."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "SpiDataWidth supported is 8, 16, 32."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "3. Configuration"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "For Level1 and Level2 operation, the SPI interrupt must be enabled. For an SE4 interrupt, the vector number is 406."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Due to memory limitations, only two SEs can be configured as SPI."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "3.1. PIN configuration"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Check the QAM8255P Pin Assignment and GPIO Configuration Spreadsheet (80-31749-1A) document."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20configure%20SAIL%20SPI/image-2024-10-28_13-41-6.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to configure SAIL SPI/image-2024-10-28_13-41-6.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Check schematic diagram"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20configure%20SAIL%20SPI/image-2024-10-23_17-56-13.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to configure SAIL SPI/image-2024-10-23_17-56-13.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20configure%20SAIL%20SPI/image-2024-10-24_10-59-12.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to configure SAIL SPI/image-2024-10-24_10-59-12.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Select the QUP I/O functions on GPIOs by writing to TLMM_GPIO_CFGn [FUNC_SEL] field."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Select and configure the serial protocol engine by writing to the QUP registers."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "PortPinMode shall select PORT_PIN_MODE_1 according to QAM8255P Pin Assignment and GPIO Configuration Spreadsheet (80-31749-1A) document."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20configure%20SAIL%20SPI/image-2024-10-28_13-52-50.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to configure SAIL SPI/image-2024-10-28_13-52-50.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20configure%20SAIL%20SPI/image-2024-10-28_13-42-57.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to configure SAIL SPI/image-2024-10-28_13-42-57.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "3.2. Protocol selection"
    },
    {
